# Project 07 – ROS2 Launch Files

## Overview

This project demonstrates how to launch multiple ROS2 nodes using a single launch file.

Instead of starting each node manually with `ros2 run`, a launch file automates the startup of an entire ROS2 application.

---

## Nodes Launched

- parameter_node
- turtlesim_node

Both nodes are started simultaneously using one command.

---

## Concepts Learned

- ROS2 Launch System
- LaunchDescription
- Node Action
- Launching Multiple Nodes
- Passing Parameters from Launch Files
- Installing Launch Files with setup.py

---

## Launch File

```python
Node(
    package='parameter_demo',
    executable='parameter_node',
    parameters=[
        {
            'message': 'Started From Launch File'
        }
    ]
)
```

---

## Build

```bash
colcon build --packages-select parameter_demo
```

---

## Launch

```bash
ros2 launch parameter_demo parameter_demo.launch.py
```

---

## Skills Demonstrated

- ROS2 Launch Files
- Multi-node Applications
- Runtime Configuration
- Python Launch API
- ROS2 Package Structure
